column2: Windy- beaver lodge on N shore- dead birch trees- no boat traffic
Windy and/or overcast for last 2 weeks- today is clear and calm
Clear- windy- few clouds- lots of floating weeds
Breezy- partly cloudy- algae- water appears thicker- many loons- eagle dove twice
Algae growth- breezy- no white caps- eagles active
Small algae particles in the water.  Calm- partly sunny.
Clear and calm 60 degrees. sighted 2 loons some ducks frogs.
Calm and clear with the temperature at 62 degrees.  Eagles loons and ducks.  Pollen accumulating on water.
Hazy but bright calm 70 degrees.  Mallard with ducklings and loons.
Clear and breezy wavy lake 62 degrees.  Panfish spawning leopard frogs.
Big clouds but sunny.  Loons sighted with young.  Weeds showing growth.
Fluffy white clouds sunny.  Small waves.
Sunny and bright with cumulus clouds.  Wild rose blooming.
Clear 75 degrees wavy.  Ideal day.  Weed growth in shallows apparent.
Sunny with some clouds.  Many white water lilies in places. frogs in weedy areas.
Sunny but hazy.  Leopard frogs and tree toads abundant many crabs.
Heavy cumulus clouds medium chop sunny.
Clear sunny day.  Viewed loon with her little one hummers still feeding.
Cloudy and calm.  Sighted mallards- loons- mergansers and heron.
Cloudy but bright. light ripple.  Loons nesting- wood ducks or hooded mergansers in tree house.
70 degrees- many cumulus clouds but bright.  Breeze with light ripple. herons- croaking frogs.
Bright sun- fluffy cumulus clouds.  Heron.
Bright- many cumulus clouds- 70 degrees.  Chop on water. eagle- ducks with broods.
Bright and breezy- white caps.  Heavy rains and high temperatures.
Sunny- blue sky- 75 degrees.  Many chipmunks- bull frogs- perch- dragonflies- white water lilies.
80 degrees- sunny. light breeze- absence of herons.
Blue sky- heavy cumulus clouds- 72 degrees.  Wavy water- apparent storm damage.
74 degree- east wind.  Water is grey-green and scummy in quiet bay.  Sighted loon with young one.
76 degrees- blue sky- clear- north wind.  Merganser and mallard broods.
69 degrees- blue sky- puffy white clouds. sea gulls- young loon- many ducks- heron.
58 degrees- blue sky- fluffy clouds- cool west wind.  Foamy water- colorful trees.
74 degrees- blue sky- cirrus clouds.  Very calm water.  Trees past peak.  One duck.
58 degrees- sunny- west wind (windy) .  Sighted 8 mergansers.  Algae is much less.
68 degrees- few clouds- sunny- two loons- mallards- osprey- wood ducks- heron- two canadian geese- and a moderate wind.
60 degrees- breezy- ripples- blue sky- and light cirrus clouds.
70 degrees- sky becoming cloudy- merganser broods- many fawns- and heavy rains yesterday.
76 degrees- blue sky- few cirrus clouds- sunny- heron feeding- and merganser brood.
72 degrees- blue sky- cirrus clouds- sunny- two loons feeding- and merganser brood.
70 degrees- blue sky- choppy water- brood of mergansers- and fluffy clouds.
74 degrees- hazy sun- small ripples- many frogs.  No ducks- loons sighted.
64 degrees- light blue sky- windy. deer and duck sightings (mallards and a black duck).
44 degrees- blue sky- sunny- bright- slightly choppy- snow on ground- and mallard in the bay.
40 degrees- blue sky- sunny with lite clouds- very calm- and no animal activity.
The temperature is 68 degrees- hazy sky- occasional sun- some wind (south) and waves.  Sighted one large otter and several mergansers.
The temperature is 68 degrees- clear blue sky- calm- saw two loons- osprey- fox and a heron.
The temperature is 65 degrees- clear blue sky- some cumulus clouds- wind- choppy water surface- and recent rains.
The temperaure is 79 degrees- light stratus clouds but sunny- blue sky- mallards with broods- osprey- bullfrogs- and heron.
The temperaure is 79 degrees- cloudless blue sky- west wind- mallards with broods- and osprey.
86 deg F. Sunny with clouds (cumulus and cirrus). Mallards with broods. Loons. Eagle- south wind
85 deg F. Weak sun. Duck and a loon- 3 sea gulls. Frogs.
72 deg F. Clear and sunny. West wind. Waves. Several sea gulls- a heron- and mallards.
62 deg F. Sunny w/ heavy cumulus clouds. Saw 2 eagles- many gulls- many mallards.
49 deg F. Clear blue sky. Sunny- west wind. Saw 2 eagles.
56 deg F- clear blue sky. A couple of mallards- some seagulls. 2 young loons. 1 eagle. South wind.
The temperature is 40 degrees- two loons- light blue sky.
The temperature is 74 degrees- mallard with ducklings- osprey- heron- frogs- loon- and clearing blue sky.
The temperature is 70 degrees- sunny- blue sky- east air motion- and loons.
Temperature is 74 degrees- sunny- light NW wind- frogs- and heavy rains past two days.
The temperature is 70 degrees- sighted loon- gulls- wood duck with four ducklings- and deer with two fawns.
Air temperature is 67 degrees F- light breeze- cloudless blue sky. Sighted 1 deer- loons- mergansers- heron- and otters.
Air temp= 42 degrees F- brisk south breeze- small waves- sunny- cloudless- gulls- sighted 2 otters and ducks.
Light blue cloudless sky.  Bright sun.  Light wind.  Mallards. Heron.  Heavy rains past few days.
68 F.  Light blue sky.  NE wind. No visible wildlife.  Light rain yesterday.
76 F- clear blue sky. Calm.  Loons with young.  Frogs.
78 F- very calm. Loons sighted (all young ones (2) now dive)
54.8 F- 1 duck in bay.  Clear blue sky.  Calm water.  Loon sighted.  Gulls. Beautiful color.
60 F- sunny- windy- small waves.  Loons- ducks.  Light blue sky.
72 F- sunny but sky isn't bright blue.  Hazy.  Loons in bay.  Loon at Deep Hole.  Heron- eagle- frogs.  Glassy calm water.
70 F- partly sunny- heavy cumulus clouds.  Westerly winds.  Choppy water.  Heron sighted.  Deer- frogs.
57 F- cloudy.  No sun.  One loon observed.
49 F- sunny- moderate SE wind.  No wildlife.  Small ripples.  Much algae!
70 F- sunny- south wind- light ripple.  Saw 3 mallard ducks.
75 F- sunny cloudless blue sky.  Brisk breeze - ripples short of white caps.  Loon- heron- bull frogs.
79 F- loon swimming and flying.  Mallard ducks - 1 with brood of eight.  Bullfrogs.
67 F- light SE wind.  Broken blue cloudy sky.  Seagulls- ducks- frogs.
52 F- light SE wind.  Clear blue sky.  Heron.  Algae.
62F- NW wind- some white caps- sunny- mallards and ducklings- herons
86F- blue sky- cumulus clouds- little ripple- light south wind- 2 loons- eagle- heron
78F- no wild life- hazy- moderate SE winds- cumulus clouds
38F- fox- ducks- loon- sunny- moderate south wind- small ripples- blue sky- cirrus clouds
Sunny beautiful day! Gentle breeze- calm.
Choppy water- breezy conditions with fast moving cloud cover.

column1: Helped by Jenny as usual. Choppy water- high fast moving clouds- helped by Jenny.

column2: Cold front conditions- very strong north wind- mostly cloudy.
Beautiful warm- sunny day with light wind.
Mostly sunny-temp 58 deg. Wind from the NW with a good chop.
NE wind with a good chop. Temp @ 48 deg.--BRRR! Grey sky with peeks of sun. Questionable temp readings as I believe the battery was failing. Springers were chasing 2 calico foxes around the point.
Partly sunny and calm with an approaching t-storm. Saw 1 eagle and the loons.

column1: As usual helped by my assistant Jenny.

column2: 1st nice day in awhile. Light boat activity. Saw a doe w/fawns on shoreline.  Sunny and calm.
Brrr!  Hard wind from the north with temps in the upper 40"s
Sunny-light chop with breeze from the north.
Air temp of 82 degrees. Hot-sunny- and hazy. Very warm recent weather. Good loon activity.

column1: Lake is higher than others around- very warm for this early- and gin clear.

column2: Sunny-beautiful blue sky- 2 loons with 2 youngsters being very vocal. 1 eagle watching them.
Beautiful day-clear blue sky- slight breeze from north
Dark drizzly day. Hard wind blowing from the SE. Temp about 50 degrees.
Temperature unit was broke so only did sechi reading.
beautiful day-sunny with a slight chop out of the north.
Sunny and windy. Good chop on the water.

48 degrees- dark sky and calm water. The ice has been out for a little over a week. Amazing!  Had not received the 2012 lake kit from the DNR so was not able to do water sampling but did clarity and temp.
Cloudy-breezy- with a little chop on the pond. Our two loons were enjoying the day and we watched a heron.
north breeze with a good chop
Blue sky and fairly calm at the deep hole.
Feels a little like fall--very nice after this scorching summer.
Late spring but finally here.  Temperature device is not operating. 2nd time one has failed. Grrr.
Another beautiful day on the pond. DNR has sent me a new temperature device. Thanks!

column1: Still not much clarity for spring--I think it may have something to do with all the runoff from the excessive rains. Just my theory.

column2: Air temp of 50F. Record cool high daytime temps. Drizzly day with a moderate north wind.

Beautiful day! Partly cloudy and bright. Gentle breeze. Water is as high as I have ever seen it in 26 years on the pond. Had a special guest help today--long time lake expert Arnie Sawatske who came along to supervise and help. A very good time. Thanks Arnie!
Mix of clouds and sun. Choppy with a good south wind.
Sunny- choppy with a pretty good NW wind.
Cool day- temp in the 50's with an east wind.
50F hard wind from the north with serious chop on the water which probably affected the sechi reading
Quiet day on the pond. Blue sky with temp of 75F. Lake has taken on the green hue.
Saw a pair of Wood ducks and an eagle low overhead while doing the readings. We have a pair of Loons on the pond again along with a Great Blue Heron I saw the evening prior.
Another beautiful day. Eagles- loons- a couple very young osprey.
dark day with occasional drizzle. Saw loons- an otter- an eagle- and a deer on Harvey's shore.
Partly cloudy- calm. 45F  Lake level extremely high from rain and snowmelt affecting clarity
2 eagles roosting on Tom's point- doe and fawn along Harvey's point. A good day.
Sunny- slight chop with a slight algae bloom happening.
Eagle flying overhead- flock of geese having their way on Trojan's old lawn. Good place for them.
